ction’."],"variants":[{"name":"Clairmont","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Adelard, Aime, Antoine, Aurore, Fernand.","French: variant of   Clermont   and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. The surname <i>Clairmont</i> is very rare in France.","In some cases possibly also English: variant of <b>Claremont</b> or   Clermont  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Simon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."],"variants":[{"name":"Simen","meanings":["Usual English form of   Simeon  , borne in the New Testament by various characters: two apostles, a brother of Jesus, a Pharisee, a leper, a tanner, a sorcerer (who offered money for the gifts of the Holy Ghost, giving rise to the term <i>simony</i>), and the man who carried Jesus's cross to the Crucifixion."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Simon I de Clermont was born in 1134, his father, Renaud de Clermont II, was 53 and his mother, Clemence de Bar, was 24. He had at least 2 sons with Mathilde of Breteuil. He died in 1187, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1134–1187":"1134–1187","1123–1173":"1123–1173","1129–Male":"1129–Surnud","1131–Male":"1131–Surnud","1133–Male":"1133–Surnud","1135–1200":"1135–1200","1137–Male":"1137–Surnud","1140–1200":"1140–1200","1143–Female":"1143–Surnud","1160–1208":"1160–1208","1175–1225":"1175–1225","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1081–1162":"1081–1162","1110–1200":"1110–1200","du 1180 au 1190":"1180 kuni 1190","1187":"1187","1110":"1110","1143":"1143","1175":"1175","1131":"1131","1162":"1162","1140":"1140","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1081":"1081","1180":"1180","1129":"1129","11